1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:35,236 --> 00:01:39,620
(One and a half years ago)

3
00:01:40,045 --> 00:01:43,045
Could you tell me
why your last job ended?

4
00:01:44,285 --> 00:01:46,006
The project I was in concluded.

5
00:01:46,366 --> 00:01:49,086
The company wanted me
to do internal data research.

6
00:01:49,526 --> 00:01:50,925
I didn't think it suited me.

7
00:01:51,045 --> 00:01:52,405
I wanted to work in operations.

8
00:01:56,366 --> 00:01:58,646
Are you sure
what you're saying now is true?

9
00:02:04,045 --> 00:02:05,606
Mr. Li, what do you think?

10
00:02:07,646 --> 00:02:08,725
I see no problem.

11
00:02:10,605 --> 00:02:11,725
I need to go. See you.

12
00:02:15,445 --> 00:02:18,845
Mr. Li, thank you
for giving me this chance.

13
00:02:19,806 --> 00:02:21,366
I shouldn't have given you this chance.

14
00:02:21,845 --> 00:02:22,920
We did a background check.

15
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:25,366
Your former boss claimed
you were fired for seducing him.

16
00:02:25,366 --> 00:02:26,285
He's lying!

17
00:02:26,486 --> 00:02:28,366
That's not true. In the office...

18
00:02:28,366 --> 00:02:29,165
He's lying,

19
00:02:29,926 --> 00:02:31,646
but weren't you lying just now?

20
00:02:34,285 --> 00:02:35,565
This industry is small.

21
00:02:35,646 --> 00:02:36,966
We always run into each other.

22
00:02:37,766 --> 00:02:39,285
Even if everyone knows he's lying,

23
00:02:39,285 --> 00:02:40,646
no one wants to get in trouble.

24
00:02:41,646 --> 00:02:42,806
Been job hunting for a while?

25
00:02:44,486 --> 00:02:45,605
Over half a year now.

26
00:02:48,046 --> 00:02:49,165
Why did you help me?

27
00:02:50,766 --> 00:02:52,125
I'm not some good soul.

28
00:02:52,845 --> 00:02:55,086
But I despise people
who collude in wrongdoing.

29
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:09,320
(Love is rushing through wind and rain)

30
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:12,808
=Episode 24=
(Sunny Tomorrow)

31
00:03:23,046 --> 00:03:23,966
You came.

32
00:03:24,246 --> 00:03:24,966
What else?

33
00:03:26,246 --> 00:03:28,125
Wait for you to ring my doorbell?

34
00:03:31,885 --> 00:03:35,285
I was waiting for you to come to me.

35
00:03:36,326 --> 00:03:37,926
But you're more patient than I imagined.

36
00:03:39,005 --> 00:03:40,165
During our last interview,

37
00:03:40,165 --> 00:03:43,685
I realized you already knew
about Mr. Li and me.

38
00:03:44,285 --> 00:03:46,926
Thinking about that now
feels quite ironic.

39
00:03:47,445 --> 00:03:48,766
You know that I know.

40
00:03:48,966 --> 00:03:50,086
I know that you know.

41
00:03:51,165 --> 00:03:52,806
Only Mr. Li didn't know

42
00:03:53,646 --> 00:03:54,685
we all know.

43
00:03:59,926 --> 00:04:01,086
What a waste of time.

44
00:04:02,486 --> 00:04:03,086
Hypocritical.

45
00:04:03,624 --> 00:04:04,840
You're the hypocritical one!

46
00:04:05,845 --> 00:04:07,165
How much longer can you stand?

47
00:04:14,326 --> 00:04:15,326
I'm the hypocritical one?

48
00:04:16,566 --> 00:04:18,126
Look at you now.

49
00:04:19,006 --> 00:04:20,845
You look glamorous,

50
00:04:22,045 --> 00:04:23,245
but at what cost?

51
00:04:24,086 --> 00:04:26,326
By taking off your clothes
and sleeping with others.

52
00:04:26,925 --> 00:04:30,725
You tried every mean
to mimic me and get close to me.

53
00:04:30,725 --> 00:04:32,086
Think that would turn you into me,

54
00:04:32,086 --> 00:04:32,766
Qiao Hailun?

55
00:04:33,886 --> 00:04:34,805
I'm warning you.

56
00:04:35,485 --> 00:04:37,045
Stop interfering in my life.

57
00:04:37,365 --> 00:04:38,646
Stop wearing my hairstyle

58
00:04:38,646 --> 00:04:39,766
to show up before me.

59
00:04:40,485 --> 00:04:42,045
I think it looks good.

60
00:04:44,966 --> 00:04:49,886
They all say this hairstyle
looks a bit dated on me.

61
00:04:53,326 --> 00:04:54,326
I like it.

62
00:04:56,326 --> 00:04:57,886
I'll make you pay!

63
00:04:57,925 --> 00:04:59,285
Think it looks good?

64
00:04:59,605 --> 00:05:00,605
What are you doing?

65
00:05:03,045 --> 00:05:04,886
Li Dongming doesn't love you at all.

66
00:05:08,526 --> 00:05:10,086
Are you afraid I'll replace you?

67
00:05:12,285 --> 00:05:14,045
Afraid I'll become you?

68
00:05:21,446 --> 00:05:22,686
You would never become me.

69
00:05:23,526 --> 00:05:25,526
Because I take every step
with a clear conscience.

70
00:05:26,646 --> 00:05:28,966
Because I hold onto my bottom line.

71
00:05:29,766 --> 00:05:30,326
And you?

72
00:05:31,446 --> 00:05:33,766
I've been working very hard.

73
00:05:35,605 --> 00:05:37,566
I've been trying hard to live.

74
00:05:39,886 --> 00:05:44,045
I just want everyone around me

75
00:05:44,886 --> 00:05:46,725
to believe I live with dignity.

76
00:05:48,485 --> 00:05:49,285
Dignity?

77
00:05:51,646 --> 00:05:52,886
Everyone around you?

78
00:05:56,126 --> 00:06:00,605
Did you think of your parents
when you said so?

79
00:06:01,725 --> 00:06:03,925
They are decent, honest people.

80
00:06:04,526 --> 00:06:08,165
They worked hard to raise you
and put you through college.

81
00:06:08,165 --> 00:06:10,845
Did they do it to let you sleep
with someone's husband?

82
00:06:10,886 --> 00:06:13,285
If they knew their daughter
stole someone's husband,

83
00:06:13,285 --> 00:06:15,405
do you think
they could hold their heads high?

84
00:06:17,405 --> 00:06:19,086
Your dad is
a high school teacher, right?

85
00:06:19,766 --> 00:06:21,165
Could he still teach at school?

86
00:06:21,165 --> 00:06:23,206
Could he look his students in the eye?

87
00:06:23,206 --> 00:06:25,086
Your mom works in the clinic.

88
00:06:25,086 --> 00:06:27,206
How could she face her colleagues?

89
00:06:27,405 --> 00:06:30,326
Could she go square dancing anymore?

90
00:06:31,045 --> 00:06:32,365
Stop it.

91
00:06:33,886 --> 00:06:35,086
Stop it.

92
00:06:35,086 --> 00:06:36,725
Did you ever think of them?

93
00:06:37,165 --> 00:06:38,526
Even just a little bit?

94
00:06:39,165 --> 00:06:42,045
What's most infuriating
is you're still so shameless now.

95
00:06:42,086 --> 00:06:45,766
Coming here so arrogantly
to talk about your efforts and dignity.

96
00:06:46,966 --> 00:06:48,245
That's not true.

97
00:06:48,245 --> 00:06:50,165
That's not true.

98
00:06:56,285 --> 00:06:57,165
Qiao Hailun.

99
00:06:57,966 --> 00:06:59,886
Stop lying to yourself.

100
00:07:00,206 --> 00:07:01,165
I'm sorry.

101
00:07:01,766 --> 00:07:03,285
I'm sorry.

102
00:07:03,285 --> 00:07:03,925
I'm sorry.

103
00:07:04,566 --> 00:07:05,845
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

104
00:07:05,845 --> 00:07:06,886
I didn't mean to.

105
00:07:07,566 --> 00:07:10,206
I just want to stay in this city.

106
00:07:10,326 --> 00:07:12,245
I just want a job.

107
00:07:12,245 --> 00:07:13,686
Am I wrong?

108
00:07:13,686 --> 00:07:14,845
Of course.

109
00:07:16,805 --> 00:07:18,326
Many people want to stay in Guangzhou.

110
00:07:18,605 --> 00:07:20,646
Would they steal other's husbands?

111
00:07:21,086 --> 00:07:22,646
Wait, what kind of solution is it?

112
00:07:22,646 --> 00:07:24,086
I had no other options.

113
00:07:26,165 --> 00:07:29,605
No one taught me what I should do.

114
00:07:30,845 --> 00:07:33,326
They told me
that studying hard was enough,

115
00:07:33,605 --> 00:07:35,326
so I studied hard.

116
00:07:35,326 --> 00:07:36,725
I've always worked hard.

117
00:07:38,086 --> 00:07:43,165
I thought everything would be fine
after graduation, after I found a job.

118
00:07:43,245 --> 00:07:45,605
But even after getting a job,
it still didn't work.

119
00:07:46,485 --> 00:07:49,326
Even if I worked 24 hours a day
without sleep,

120
00:07:49,566 --> 00:07:52,605
I still couldn't compete
with those who are smart, sensitive,

121
00:07:52,886 --> 00:07:55,245
and with abilities to land clients.

122
00:07:57,165 --> 00:07:59,045
My performance wasn't the worst,

123
00:07:59,605 --> 00:08:01,805
yet they still fired me.

124
00:08:02,165 --> 00:08:04,126
What other option do I have?

125
00:08:05,805 --> 00:08:08,845
You still refuse to see this
as your own fault?

126
00:08:10,566 --> 00:08:12,326
It was your choice.

127
00:08:12,365 --> 00:08:14,566
You chose to sell your body and soul.

128
00:08:14,566 --> 00:08:15,605
Who else can you blame?

129
00:08:16,245 --> 00:08:18,646
You can only blame yourself
for being weak,

130
00:08:18,766 --> 00:08:20,446
letting others trample over you

131
00:08:20,446 --> 00:08:21,126
and ignore you,

132
00:08:21,126 --> 00:08:23,165
without even resisting at all.

133
00:08:24,886 --> 00:08:25,566
Qiao Hailun,

134
00:08:26,766 --> 00:08:28,805
do you think you're the victim?

135
00:08:28,805 --> 00:08:31,566
No. You're just pathetic.

136
00:08:35,566 --> 00:08:36,125
Pathetic.

137
00:08:38,046 --> 00:08:40,406
I could only choose
between dignity and my job.

138
00:08:41,365 --> 00:08:44,005
You wouldn't understand
how tough I live.

139
00:08:44,365 --> 00:08:44,966
How tough!

140
00:08:45,605 --> 00:08:46,645
How tough!

141
00:08:47,605 --> 00:08:48,605
But I made it.

142
00:08:49,245 --> 00:08:50,485
I made it.

143
00:08:50,686 --> 00:08:52,206
I didn't get fired.

144
00:08:55,605 --> 00:08:57,605
Life is tough for everyone.

145
00:09:00,286 --> 00:09:01,005
Including you,

146
00:09:01,966 --> 00:09:02,926
your parents,

147
00:09:03,845 --> 00:09:06,086
and many people around me.

148
00:09:07,086 --> 00:09:09,926
But not everyone
chooses the path you took.

149
00:09:10,485 --> 00:09:12,206
And now, you should realize

150
00:09:12,206 --> 00:09:13,446
this path isn't easier.

151
00:09:17,566 --> 00:09:18,566
You're still young.

152
00:09:20,125 --> 00:09:20,845
I advise you...

153
00:09:26,446 --> 00:09:27,880
to turn back before it's too late.

154
00:09:37,245 --> 00:09:39,845
What would you do if you were me?

155
00:09:41,605 --> 00:09:44,566
I just want a job!

156
00:09:48,086 --> 00:09:50,885
No one taught me what to do.

157
00:09:52,166 --> 00:09:54,086
I'm such a fool.

158
00:09:56,686 --> 00:09:58,645
How could I be such a fool?

159
00:10:03,406 --> 00:10:04,725
Life is tough.

160
00:10:06,446 --> 00:10:07,525
How tough!

161
00:10:55,885 --> 00:10:56,365
Shut it.

162
00:12:04,406 --> 00:12:04,966
Thank you.

163
00:12:18,125 --> 00:12:18,725
Hold me.

164
00:12:42,765 --> 00:12:43,725
You play guitar?

165
00:12:46,645 --> 00:12:47,125
Yes.

166
00:12:48,605 --> 00:12:49,446
I'll play it for you.

167
00:15:10,920 --> 00:15:13,448
(Hetai Center)

168
00:15:15,525 --> 00:15:16,566
The smell is much better.

169
00:15:17,485 --> 00:15:18,365
Don't worry.

170
00:15:18,365 --> 00:15:20,005
I already checked with the doctor.

171
00:15:20,005 --> 00:15:23,125
He said the aromatherapy scent
won't affect your health.

172
00:15:23,125 --> 00:15:23,765
Rest assured.

173
00:15:25,245 --> 00:15:28,645
Why are you so late?

174
00:15:30,125 --> 00:15:32,286
How dare you pick on me
even before discharge?

175
00:15:32,605 --> 00:15:34,005
Want me to leave?

176
00:15:34,765 --> 00:15:36,005
You're threatening me again.

177
00:15:36,885 --> 00:15:38,806
I'm not threatening you.

178
00:15:39,046 --> 00:15:42,046
Man, I have to work, okay?

179
00:15:42,525 --> 00:15:45,286
I'd still be asleep
at this hour normally.

180
00:15:45,286 --> 00:15:46,926
You messed up my schedule.

181
00:15:47,686 --> 00:15:48,765
Let me tell you.

182
00:15:48,765 --> 00:15:50,166
I'm leaving at 4:30 PM.

183
00:15:52,485 --> 00:15:53,406
Come closer.

184
00:15:58,245 --> 00:16:00,806
There's something behind the pillow.

185
00:16:01,525 --> 00:16:02,605
Get it for me.

186
00:16:09,525 --> 00:16:10,446
What for?

187
00:16:13,765 --> 00:16:14,566
Open it.

188
00:16:15,046 --> 00:16:16,046
I'm not opening it.

189
00:16:19,605 --> 00:16:20,966
Then I'll open it for you.

190
00:16:21,286 --> 00:16:22,365
Don't...

191
00:16:22,365 --> 00:16:23,845
Don't touch me! My heart!

192
00:16:25,365 --> 00:16:26,406
Playing the victim now?

193
00:16:26,645 --> 00:16:27,326
Don't open it.

194
00:16:28,645 --> 00:16:30,926
Don't open it.

195
00:16:35,885 --> 00:16:37,005
Listen to me.

196
00:16:38,926 --> 00:16:40,566
I'm an old man already.

197
00:16:42,885 --> 00:16:45,885
Even with advanced medicine...

198
00:16:48,806 --> 00:16:51,525
If something like this happens again,

199
00:16:54,125 --> 00:16:55,166
I might...

200
00:16:57,806 --> 00:16:58,406
So,

201
00:17:01,086 --> 00:17:02,446
I'm anxious.

202
00:17:05,285 --> 00:17:07,245
I've had many women in my life,

203
00:17:12,525 --> 00:17:14,005
but only you

204
00:17:16,206 --> 00:17:18,406
who genuinely care about me

205
00:17:19,805 --> 00:17:21,166
and not for my money.

206
00:17:23,725 --> 00:17:24,805
I wonder

207
00:17:27,285 --> 00:17:28,926
if you want to marry me.

208
00:17:30,886 --> 00:17:31,765
Don't worry.

209
00:17:33,166 --> 00:17:36,005
I won't ask you to sign a prenup.

210
00:17:39,565 --> 00:17:43,886
What's mine is yours, okay?

211
00:17:45,525 --> 00:17:46,805
Give me some time.

212
00:17:48,485 --> 00:17:50,606
You can take a look first.

213
00:17:50,886 --> 00:17:51,805
Try it.

214
00:17:51,805 --> 00:17:53,045
No.

215
00:17:53,045 --> 00:17:55,245
Don't open it, seriously.

216
00:17:55,565 --> 00:17:56,446
What's going on here?

217
00:17:58,126 --> 00:17:58,926
Are you two married?

218
00:17:59,166 --> 00:18:00,166
No, not yet.

219
00:18:00,166 --> 00:18:01,446
Don't get us wrong. Have a seat.

220
00:18:01,846 --> 00:18:02,686
Not yet?

221
00:18:03,805 --> 00:18:04,686
What are you doing?

222
00:18:05,166 --> 00:18:06,126
Are you proposing?

223
00:18:06,565 --> 00:18:07,206
Are you crazy?

224
00:18:07,485 --> 00:18:08,725
This doesn't concern you.

225
00:18:08,725 --> 00:18:09,325
Get out.

226
00:18:09,525 --> 00:18:11,005
Seems what they said is true.

227
00:18:11,886 --> 00:18:13,245
You really have your eye on her.

228
00:18:14,045 --> 00:18:15,285
She's just a liquor promoter.

229
00:18:15,565 --> 00:18:17,325
Can you believe what this lowlife says?

230
00:18:17,646 --> 00:18:18,966
I told you to get out.

231
00:18:18,966 --> 00:18:20,646
Mind your words!

232
00:18:20,646 --> 00:18:21,646
Why should I get out?

233
00:18:21,646 --> 00:18:22,765
You can't kick me out.

234
00:18:23,285 --> 00:18:24,805
I can tolerate you hooking up women.

235
00:18:25,366 --> 00:18:27,045
But don't bring me any stepmother.

236
00:18:27,166 --> 00:18:27,846
And you.

237
00:18:28,926 --> 00:18:31,525
My words are mean, but true.

238
00:18:31,926 --> 00:18:33,045
What are you scheming?

239
00:18:33,406 --> 00:18:34,846
Seeing my dad lying in a ward,

240
00:18:34,846 --> 00:18:36,765
you think you can become Mrs. Shen?

241
00:18:37,166 --> 00:18:38,245
Dream on!

242
00:18:38,245 --> 00:18:39,765
With me here, impossible!

243
00:18:40,085 --> 00:18:44,085
Deng, suspend
Shen Xing's dividends next month.

244
00:18:44,085 --> 00:18:44,805
Stop that!

245
00:18:44,805 --> 00:18:45,446
Give me that.

246
00:18:45,646 --> 00:18:47,446
He just had surgery. Don't touch him.

247
00:18:47,446 --> 00:18:48,565
Call Lawyer Tang over.

248
00:18:48,805 --> 00:18:50,166
- Come see me tomorrow.
- Come out!

249
00:18:50,926 --> 00:18:51,686
Just wait!

250
00:18:52,846 --> 00:18:54,686
You're so strong! Let me go!

251
00:18:57,206 --> 00:18:58,166
This is a hospital.

252
00:18:58,485 --> 00:18:59,805
Your dad just had surgery.

253
00:18:59,805 --> 00:19:01,926
You couldn't sell liquor,
so you're selling yourself?

254
00:19:04,765 --> 00:19:05,966
How dare you hit me?

255
00:19:07,366 --> 00:19:08,245
I'm telling you,

256
00:19:08,485 --> 00:19:10,485
I've never lost a fight with a woman.

257
00:19:10,485 --> 00:19:12,712
I don't care about the issues
between you and your dad.

258
00:19:12,712 --> 00:19:14,126
But if you dare insult me,

259
00:19:14,525 --> 00:19:15,926
I'll hit you every time I see you.

260
00:19:15,926 --> 00:19:16,805
Got it?

261
00:19:16,805 --> 00:19:17,725
You shrew...

262
00:19:19,752 --> 00:19:21,485
Stop, please.

263
00:19:24,045 --> 00:19:25,446
I mean well.

264
00:19:25,446 --> 00:19:26,525
My dad isn't any good man.

265
00:19:26,525 --> 00:19:27,366
He'll destroy you.

266
00:19:27,366 --> 00:19:28,245
None of your business.

267
00:19:29,606 --> 00:19:31,245
Wait, ma'am.

268
00:19:34,045 --> 00:19:35,886
I could agree to you two
getting married,

269
00:19:36,126 --> 00:19:37,325
but on one condition.

270
00:19:37,886 --> 00:19:39,485
Get him to give me some money, okay?

271
00:19:41,725 --> 00:19:42,245
I...

272
00:19:43,285 --> 00:19:44,805
Insane.

273
00:19:57,565 --> 00:19:58,325
Please come in.

274
00:19:59,765 --> 00:20:02,325
Please wait a moment.
Mr. Li's meeting will end soon.

275
00:20:02,325 --> 00:20:02,846
Thank you.

276
00:20:35,406 --> 00:20:37,325
A meeting came up.
Sorry to keep you waiting.

277
00:20:43,166 --> 00:20:46,765
I've successfully signed many contracts
and agreements in this room.

278
00:20:47,886 --> 00:20:51,126
But I'm not so confident
about this agreement today.

279
00:20:52,085 --> 00:20:54,846
So I wanted to borrow
a bit of luck from this place.

280
00:20:55,886 --> 00:20:56,525
Thank you

281
00:20:56,805 --> 00:20:57,846
for making this trip here.

282
00:21:00,166 --> 00:21:00,966
Not at all.

283
00:21:04,886 --> 00:21:05,606
Take this.

284
00:21:17,805 --> 00:21:19,485
You have all the WeChat chat records.

285
00:21:21,166 --> 00:21:22,045
Quite detailed.

286
00:21:23,725 --> 00:21:25,966
I've also deleted all the photos
from the phone.

287
00:21:26,805 --> 00:21:27,926
Now you can rest assured.

288
00:21:47,926 --> 00:21:51,606
I still need you
to sign this confidentiality agreement.

289
00:21:55,966 --> 00:21:59,206
Don't publicly announce
our divorce for one year.

290
00:21:59,846 --> 00:22:03,846
If asked later, just say
we divorced due to incompatibility.

291
00:22:07,085 --> 00:22:08,725
Mr. Li, you really are thoughtful.

292
00:22:25,612 --> 00:22:27,487
(Divorce Agreement)

293
00:22:58,085 --> 00:22:58,646
Thank you.

294
00:22:59,725 --> 00:23:00,485
No problem.

295
00:23:10,765 --> 00:23:11,926
(It's all over.)

296
00:23:13,446 --> 00:23:15,765
(I can finally stand here
openly and honestly,)

297
00:23:16,206 --> 00:23:17,686
(feeling the warmth of sunlight.)

298
00:23:19,485 --> 00:23:23,646
(It feels good to start fresh.)

299
00:24:05,646 --> 00:24:06,446
Who is that?

300
00:24:06,446 --> 00:24:07,245
Qiao Hailun.

301
00:24:08,846 --> 00:24:09,886
Seems like she fainted.

302
00:24:10,325 --> 00:24:11,126
Go check on her.

303
00:24:11,245 --> 00:24:12,886
Wait, I-I can't.

304
00:24:13,045 --> 00:24:14,325
Why don't you go check?

305
00:24:14,325 --> 00:24:16,085
Didn't you learn first aid? Go.

306
00:24:16,085 --> 00:24:17,926
She just fainted.

307
00:24:18,166 --> 00:24:19,126
Exactly.

308
00:24:19,126 --> 00:24:20,525
- Help her up.
- Help her up.

309
00:24:22,725 --> 00:24:23,366
Qiao Hailun.

310
00:24:23,606 --> 00:24:24,606
Mr. Li's wife is here.

311
00:24:25,406 --> 00:24:26,245
Step back.

312
00:24:29,886 --> 00:24:30,485
Qiao Hailun.

313
00:24:32,406 --> 00:24:33,005
Qiao Hailun.

314
00:24:36,366 --> 00:24:37,366
What are you waiting for?

315
00:24:37,366 --> 00:24:38,166
Call an ambulance!

316
00:24:38,166 --> 00:24:38,805
I'll go call.

317
00:24:39,646 --> 00:24:40,245
Qiao Hailun.

318
00:24:49,966 --> 00:24:50,646
What happened?

319
00:24:58,728 --> 00:25:02,276
(Is there a defibrillator?)

320
00:25:03,112 --> 00:25:04,406
Heard it? Get the defibrillator!

321
00:25:04,406 --> 00:25:04,725
Okay.

322
00:25:08,725 --> 00:25:09,525
Qiao Hailun.

323
00:25:24,966 --> 00:25:25,725
Qiao Hailun.

324
00:25:27,126 --> 00:25:28,126
Qiao Hailun.

325
00:25:33,765 --> 00:25:34,565
Qiao Hailun.

326
00:25:39,085 --> 00:25:39,886
Qiao Hailun.

327
00:25:43,966 --> 00:25:44,805
Qiao Hailun.

328
00:28:07,525 --> 00:28:08,406
Don't try to avoid it.

329
00:28:09,446 --> 00:28:10,686
Ms. Zhao, what brings you here?

330
00:28:17,285 --> 00:28:21,126
I-I had nowhere to go,

331
00:28:22,126 --> 00:28:23,045
so came to see you all.

332
00:28:26,525 --> 00:28:27,765
Am I interrupting?

333
00:28:28,285 --> 00:28:29,565
- No.
- Not at all.

334
00:28:29,565 --> 00:28:30,606
- No.
- No.

335
00:28:30,606 --> 00:28:31,886
Ms. Zhao, come in.

336
00:28:31,966 --> 00:28:33,085
We've got lots of snacks.

337
00:28:33,126 --> 00:28:34,245
Set a place for Ms. Zhao.

338
00:28:34,646 --> 00:28:36,005
Got it, go get a chair.

339
00:28:37,646 --> 00:28:39,245
Here, I'll take your bag.

340
00:28:39,926 --> 00:28:40,686
Have a seat.

341
00:28:41,926 --> 00:28:43,126
It's the New Year.

342
00:28:43,646 --> 00:28:45,646
- So we gather tonight.
- Right.

343
00:28:45,646 --> 00:28:47,366
Soon we'll pack up and head home.

344
00:28:48,565 --> 00:28:49,245
Come on, sit.

345
00:28:49,886 --> 00:28:50,886
Don't be polite. Sit.

346
00:28:50,886 --> 00:28:51,446
Ms. Zhao, sit.

347
00:28:51,966 --> 00:28:54,565
Ms. Zhao, let's have a toast.

348
00:28:55,485 --> 00:28:57,245
Although my wine might not be very good.

349
00:29:01,805 --> 00:29:03,406
Gennadiy 12 Year Old.

350
00:29:05,166 --> 00:29:07,166
I handled the launch event
for this wine too.

351
00:29:07,926 --> 00:29:08,725
This wine is good.

352
00:29:09,085 --> 00:29:09,846
Great.

353
00:29:10,446 --> 00:29:12,325
Ms. Zhao, we need to toast with this.

354
00:29:12,325 --> 00:29:13,085
I'll pour for you.

355
00:29:13,765 --> 00:29:16,366
Ms. Zhao, try my secret sauce.

356
00:29:18,646 --> 00:29:20,805
Let's welcome Ms. Zhao, bottoms up!

357
00:29:20,805 --> 00:29:21,285
Welcome!

358
00:29:21,285 --> 00:29:22,646
- Okay, Happy New Year!
- Welcome!

359
00:29:22,646 --> 00:29:23,606
- Come on!
- Happy New Year!

360
00:29:23,606 --> 00:29:25,366
- Happy New Year!
- Happy New Year!

361
00:29:25,805 --> 00:29:26,646
Let me tell you.

362
00:29:27,085 --> 00:29:28,366
When I go home this year,

363
00:29:28,846 --> 00:29:31,325
if anyone asks me again
when I plan to get married...

364
00:29:32,085 --> 00:29:32,926
What would you say?

365
00:29:33,886 --> 00:29:35,406
I'll ask them how much they saved.

366
00:29:35,886 --> 00:29:38,045
I'll mention their sore spot.

367
00:29:38,045 --> 00:29:38,886
- Deal with them.
- Deal with them.

368
00:29:38,886 --> 00:29:39,846
- Great!
- Yeah!

369
00:29:41,045 --> 00:29:44,325
This New Year, I'm bringing him home.

370
00:29:47,606 --> 00:29:50,926
Okay. Congrats!

371
00:29:52,646 --> 00:29:54,886
Zixuan, only you left.

372
00:29:54,886 --> 00:29:55,206
Right.

373
00:29:55,206 --> 00:29:55,725
What?

374
00:29:55,886 --> 00:29:57,045
We set you up with someone.

375
00:29:57,406 --> 00:29:59,886
That's not my life goal right now.

376
00:30:01,846 --> 00:30:03,485
You've joined a big company.

377
00:30:03,565 --> 00:30:05,085
Even your speech sounds so refined.

378
00:30:05,085 --> 00:30:06,646
I'm flattered.

379
00:30:07,926 --> 00:30:08,966
Life goal...

380
00:30:09,886 --> 00:30:11,725
I have no life goals.

381
00:30:11,725 --> 00:30:12,686
Isn't that just fine?

382
00:30:12,686 --> 00:30:13,166
Right.

383
00:30:13,846 --> 00:30:14,805
Let's play a game.

384
00:30:15,206 --> 00:30:15,846
How to play?

385
00:30:16,126 --> 00:30:17,166
One sentence per person.

386
00:30:17,485 --> 00:30:21,805
The sentence has
to start with "I have never..."

387
00:30:21,886 --> 00:30:22,966
Give us an example.

388
00:30:23,166 --> 00:30:27,406
For example, I have never
scored a hundred on a test.

389
00:30:27,646 --> 00:30:29,406
Then anyone who has scored a hundred

390
00:30:29,406 --> 00:30:30,805
has to drink a penalty shot.

391
00:30:31,126 --> 00:30:31,485
Deal.

392
00:30:31,485 --> 00:30:32,285
Understood.

393
00:30:32,446 --> 00:30:33,085
Let's go.

394
00:30:33,085 --> 00:30:33,606
I'll start.

395
00:30:34,325 --> 00:30:36,285
I have never

396
00:30:37,206 --> 00:30:38,085
been married.

397
00:30:41,805 --> 00:30:42,366
I'll drink.

398
00:30:43,686 --> 00:30:44,446
Ms. Zhao!

399
00:30:44,485 --> 00:30:45,406
You're the best!

400
00:30:45,406 --> 00:30:46,166
Awesome!

401
00:30:48,045 --> 00:30:49,206
Next one. Hurry!

402
00:30:49,565 --> 00:30:51,325
I have never been in a relationship.

403
00:30:51,646 --> 00:30:52,646
Cut it out!

404
00:30:53,085 --> 00:30:54,805
Who believes that? Stop pretending.

405
00:30:55,208 --> 00:30:56,966
Seriously, I've never been
in a relationship.

406
00:30:56,966 --> 00:30:57,805
Come on.

407
00:31:00,886 --> 00:31:01,646
So by your logic,

408
00:31:01,646 --> 00:31:02,446
I should say,

409
00:31:02,446 --> 00:31:04,005
I have never been divorced.

410
00:31:04,285 --> 00:31:05,646
- Who has?
- Who's ever been divorced?

411
00:31:05,646 --> 00:31:06,646
Can I say it like that?

412
00:31:06,646 --> 00:31:07,406
No.

413
00:31:07,406 --> 00:31:08,366
Why?

414
00:31:09,085 --> 00:31:10,285
I have been divorced.

415
00:31:10,926 --> 00:31:11,646
I'll drink.

416
00:31:16,968 --> 00:31:17,446
I'll drink.

417
00:31:17,446 --> 00:31:18,446
N-Next one.

418
00:31:18,446 --> 00:31:18,886
Whose turn?

419
00:31:18,886 --> 00:31:19,765
My turn.

420
00:31:20,126 --> 00:31:24,485
I have never earned
over 10,000 yuan a month.

421
00:31:25,366 --> 00:31:26,206
Me neither.

422
00:31:26,926 --> 00:31:28,886
- Why are you drinking?
- Why are you drinking?

423
00:31:29,565 --> 00:31:31,085
I-I-I have.

424
00:31:31,085 --> 00:31:32,446
That's insulting.

425
00:31:32,646 --> 00:31:33,606
That's bullying.

426
00:31:36,765 --> 00:31:38,085
Next is Ms. Zhao.

427
00:31:38,406 --> 00:31:39,325
Ms. Zhao, your turn.

428
00:31:39,325 --> 00:31:39,966
It's your turn.

429
00:31:39,966 --> 00:31:40,565
Ms. Zhao.

430
00:31:44,406 --> 00:31:47,446
I have never...

431
00:31:54,606 --> 00:31:55,646
felt this awful before.

432
00:32:09,406 --> 00:32:10,406
Everyone lost.

433
00:32:10,406 --> 00:32:11,646
Drink up!

434
00:32:11,646 --> 00:32:12,646
Let's all have a drink!

435
00:32:12,646 --> 00:32:13,646
Ms. Zhao, let's drink!

436
00:32:13,646 --> 00:32:14,206
Have a drink!

437
00:32:14,206 --> 00:32:14,886
- All together.
- Ms. Zhao.

438
00:32:20,886 --> 00:32:21,805
I have a suggestion.

439
00:32:22,206 --> 00:32:23,886
How about we sing a song?

440
00:32:24,085 --> 00:32:24,805
Sure.

441
00:32:24,805 --> 00:32:25,126
Right?

442
00:32:25,126 --> 00:32:26,166
What should we sing?

443
00:32:26,166 --> 00:32:27,366
You start.

444
00:32:27,406 --> 00:32:28,525
I'll do it.

445
00:32:29,366 --> 00:32:30,966
♪Flowers in my heart♪

446
00:32:31,406 --> 00:32:34,126
♪I want to take you home♪

447
00:32:34,686 --> 00:32:36,686
♪In that late-night bar♪

448
00:32:36,725 --> 00:32:39,285
♪Who cares if it's real or fake♪

449
00:32:40,126 --> 00:32:41,765
♪Sway freely♪

450
00:32:42,285 --> 00:32:44,366
♪Forget the one you like♪

451
00:34:25,286 --> 00:34:27,926
So she had depression long ago?

452
00:34:28,406 --> 00:34:29,926
It might not be depression.

453
00:34:29,926 --> 00:34:31,005
It hasn't been diagnosed.

454
00:34:31,366 --> 00:34:34,565
But she did go to counseling
in our building several times.

455
00:34:35,085 --> 00:34:36,286
I didn't even know

456
00:34:36,286 --> 00:34:38,806
we had a counseling office
in this building.

457
00:34:39,326 --> 00:34:40,685
Fortunately, she got counseling.

458
00:34:40,685 --> 00:34:42,024
If really death from overwork,

459
00:34:42,024 --> 00:34:43,688
the company would suffer
in compensation.

460
00:34:43,766 --> 00:34:45,645
Isn't it death from overwork?

461
00:34:47,366 --> 00:34:49,366
I wonder how much
the company will compensate.

462
00:34:50,726 --> 00:34:52,846
What's the point?

463
00:34:53,366 --> 00:34:54,366
She is already gone.

464
00:34:55,485 --> 00:34:56,446
Our calculations show

465
00:34:56,446 --> 00:34:59,165
compensation for Qiao Hailun's death
should be around 500,000 yuan.

466
00:34:59,645 --> 00:35:01,886
The company can add
two to three hundred thousand.

467
00:35:02,205 --> 00:35:04,366
Plus, all our employees enjoy insurance.

468
00:35:04,366 --> 00:35:06,605
She could get 600,000 yuan
in death benefits.

469
00:35:06,846 --> 00:35:08,286
That adds up to quite a bit.

470
00:35:09,896 --> 00:35:11,144
Compensate her two million.

471
00:35:11,846 --> 00:35:14,926
Count the rest
as the maximum year-end bonus.

472
00:35:16,165 --> 00:35:17,366
Two million might be...

473
00:35:18,886 --> 00:35:19,806
What's wrong with that?

474
00:35:20,726 --> 00:35:21,645
Is that a lot?

475
00:35:21,806 --> 00:35:23,085
That's a human life.

476
00:35:24,645 --> 00:35:26,366
She had a brain hemorrhage
at the office.

477
00:35:26,726 --> 00:35:29,926
And she'd been at the office for
dozens of hours straight before death.

478
00:35:30,926 --> 00:35:33,246
If her family kicks up a fuss,
will two million cover it?

479
00:35:35,726 --> 00:35:38,246
Fine, I'll report it as two million.

480
00:35:40,685 --> 00:35:42,326
Go ahead.
Send the email, I'll approve it.

481
00:35:43,685 --> 00:35:44,360
Yes.

482
00:35:45,205 --> 00:35:46,246
Picked her family up?

483
00:35:47,165 --> 00:35:47,886
Yes.

484
00:35:48,165 --> 00:35:49,446
Only her parents came.

485
00:35:54,726 --> 00:35:55,565
I'll step out now.

486
00:36:09,605 --> 00:36:11,165
Sir, Ma'am, no need to see us out.

487
00:36:14,286 --> 00:36:14,926
Mr. Li.

488
00:36:16,165 --> 00:36:17,645
You're a good man.

489
00:36:19,766 --> 00:36:20,446
Hailun

490
00:36:21,005 --> 00:36:24,846
was lucky to have a boss like you.

491
00:36:28,005 --> 00:36:28,766
Thank you.

492
00:36:30,446 --> 00:36:33,726
Thank you for your care
and mentoring for Hailun,

493
00:36:34,205 --> 00:36:38,525
and for helping us
get so much compensation.

494
00:36:39,685 --> 00:36:40,286
Thank you.

495
00:36:41,246 --> 00:36:45,806
Hailun would be grateful from beyond.

496
00:36:47,446 --> 00:36:48,125
Thank you.

497
00:37:02,125 --> 00:37:02,926
Everyone, go home.

498
00:37:02,926 --> 00:37:04,328
No need to go back to the office.

499
00:37:04,565 --> 00:37:06,645
Okay, drive safely, Mr. Li.

500
00:38:02,246 --> 00:38:03,366
Move!

501
00:38:03,366 --> 00:38:04,525
Brakes failed! Move!

502
00:38:06,565 --> 00:38:08,205
Sorry! Are you okay?

503
00:38:08,806 --> 00:38:10,045
Watch the road!

504
00:38:10,446 --> 00:38:12,485
I'm sorry. The brakes failed.

505
00:38:19,656 --> 00:38:21,806
(Tiande Center)

506
00:38:21,806 --> 00:38:24,605
(Recently, our company's
Senior Partner Li Dongming)

507
00:38:24,966 --> 00:38:28,085
(was involved in an accident
while visiting a colleague's family.)

508
00:38:28,485 --> 00:38:32,846
(He was diagnosed a comminuted fracture
of a single lumbar vertebra.)

509
00:38:33,286 --> 00:38:36,446
(He will take an indefinite unpaid leave,
effective immediately.)

510
00:38:43,926 --> 00:38:44,966
This is your desk.

511
00:38:44,966 --> 00:38:45,766
Happy onboarding.

512
00:38:45,766 --> 00:38:46,286
Thank you.

513
00:38:59,766 --> 00:39:01,966
Nice to meet you. I'm the new colleague.

514
00:39:02,125 --> 00:39:03,326
My name is Zhao Yanan.

515
00:39:08,085 --> 00:39:08,766
Nice to meet you.

516
00:39:09,406 --> 00:39:10,525
I'm new here.

517
00:39:10,525 --> 00:39:11,766
My name is Zhao Yanan.

518
00:39:11,806 --> 00:39:12,806
Submit it this afternoon.

519
00:39:15,525 --> 00:39:17,886
Nice to meet you. I'm Zhao Yanan.

520
00:39:17,886 --> 00:39:19,366
New here.

521
00:39:31,886 --> 00:39:32,446
Come in.

522
00:39:35,766 --> 00:39:37,286
Then you'll handle it.

523
00:39:37,525 --> 00:39:40,246
Don't worry. I'm now in charge
of the entire VIP club.

524
00:39:40,246 --> 00:39:41,806
I'll get it all sorted with one call.

525
00:39:42,806 --> 00:39:43,846
Awesome, Danning.

526
00:39:44,366 --> 00:39:45,565
Go, Mei.

527
00:39:53,005 --> 00:39:54,205
Ms. Zhao, wanted to see me?

528
00:39:55,565 --> 00:39:56,525
Show you something.

529
00:40:00,552 --> 00:40:02,792
(China Division Promotional Team
Promotion Proposal)

530
00:40:06,565 --> 00:40:08,326
This proposal is...

531
00:40:08,726 --> 00:40:11,085
The company will open
internal positions for promoters,

532
00:40:11,966 --> 00:40:13,766
and we will all have
promotion opportunities?

533
00:40:13,966 --> 00:40:17,165
Yes, take this back
and review it carefully.

534
00:40:18,406 --> 00:40:20,886
Any questions, feel free to raise them.

535
00:40:28,766 --> 00:40:29,326
Thank you.

536
00:40:30,645 --> 00:40:31,286
No problem.

537
00:40:45,960 --> 00:40:47,222
(Dong Yue)

538
00:41:12,520 --> 00:41:14,504
(Dong Yue)

539
00:41:19,336 --> 00:41:20,168
Hello.

540
00:41:20,326 --> 00:41:21,446
(After all these,)

541
00:41:22,286 --> 00:41:23,846
(I've finally arrived here.)

542
00:41:24,685 --> 00:41:27,085
(This city remains endlessly vast.)

543
00:41:27,766 --> 00:41:28,886
(Yet in my entire life,)

544
00:41:29,366 --> 00:41:31,605
(I've never felt
as certain as I do now.)

545
00:41:32,406 --> 00:41:34,726
(Sunlight falls on my face,)

546
00:41:35,165 --> 00:41:36,565
(and wind blows through my hair.)

547
00:41:37,165 --> 00:41:38,726
(Someone calls my name.)

548
00:41:39,165 --> 00:41:40,446
(I'm still alive and well)

549
00:41:40,766 --> 00:41:42,806
(and can still see
people coming and going.)

550
00:41:43,605 --> 00:41:47,045
(In them, I see shadows of many people.)

551
00:41:47,926 --> 00:41:50,005
(Perhaps death
is not the opposite of life,)

552
00:41:50,246 --> 00:41:52,605
(but exists eternally as part of life.)

553
00:41:54,125 --> 00:41:55,565
(Play Miracle, Music Box)
(Those who made me laugh,)

554
00:41:55,565 --> 00:41:56,766
(cried with me,)

555
00:41:57,205 --> 00:41:58,766
(chatted with me all night,)

556
00:41:59,005 --> 00:42:01,326
(traveled far to visit me,)

557
00:42:01,766 --> 00:42:03,446
(always prioritized me,)

558
00:42:04,286 --> 00:42:06,246
(and said they missed and loved me,)

559
00:42:07,406 --> 00:42:10,886
(they have always been here.)

560
00:42:35,243 --> 00:42:39,983
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

561
00:42:44,433 --> 00:42:46,353
♪Too much of shame♪

562
00:42:46,699 --> 00:42:49,495
♪To waste it crying♪

563
00:42:51,953 --> 00:42:53,873
♪Leave all behind you♪

564
00:42:53,873 --> 00:42:56,153
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

565
00:42:56,273 --> 00:42:58,502
♪You know how far you've gone♪

566
00:42:58,637 --> 00:43:00,913
♪In the fire you rise again♪

567
00:43:01,099 --> 00:43:03,459
♪You made it through the worst♪

568
00:43:03,597 --> 00:43:05,801
♪The best is yet to come♪

569
